  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Strategy for Preventing the Consumption and Distribution of Psychoactive Substances by Children and Adolescents in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project contributes to the development and implementation of actions to prevent the use and exploitation of children and adolescents in the commission of criminal activities, as part of a comprehensive policy to address the drug problem in Colombia. To address this issue, the project adopts two main lines of action. Implementation of the Strong Families Program which strengthens and empowers 1,200 families to carry out activities to prevent adolescents and young people in the commission of criminal activities by preventing the use of psychoactive substances based on their co-responsibility for guaranteeing and protecting the rights of children and adolescents. The project will also design and implement strategies with a migration approach to prevent the use of children and adolescents in criminal activities associated with the distribution and commercialization of illicit drugs in territories affected by the distribution and marketing of illicit drugs.</narrative>
  </description>
